This paper deals with the study of degrees of freedom (DoF) in cellular networks with full duplex (FD) base stations equipped with multiple antennas. The paper focuses on the use of interference alignment and beamforming techniques to allocate UL and DL information streams. This topic is closely related to information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). Additionally, the use of multiple antennas and beamforming techniques suggests that the paper may also be relevant to multimedia (cs.MM) and communication engineering (cs.CE). Finally, the paper deals with cellular networks, which suggests that it may also be relevant to social and information networks (cs.SI).
